{"orig":"/Users/kalaverin/src/lang/nim/lib/pure/options.nim","nimble":"stdlib","moduleDescription":"<p>This module implements types which encapsulate an optional value.</p>\n<p>A value of type <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt> either contains a value <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> (represented as <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">some</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt>) or is empty (<tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">none</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt>).</p>\n<p>This can be useful when you have a value that can be present or not. The absence of a value is often represented by <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Keyword\">nil</span></span></tt>, but that is not always available, nor is it always a good solution.</p>\n\n<h1><a class=\"toc-backref\" id=\"basic-usage\" href=\"#basic-usage\">Basic usage</a></h1><p>Let's start with an example: a procedure that finds the index of a character in a string. </p>\nThe <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">get</span></span></tt> operation demonstrated above returns the underlying value, or raises <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">UnpackDefect</span></span></tt> if there is no value. Note that <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">UnpackDefect</span></span></tt> inherits from <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">system</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">Defect</span></span></tt> and should therefore never be caught. Instead, rely on checking if the option contains a value with the <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#isSome,Option[T]\">isSome</a> and <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#isNone,Option[T]\">isNone</a> procs.\n<h1><a class=\"toc-backref\" id=\"pattern-matching\" href=\"#pattern-matching\">Pattern matching</a></h1><div class=\"admonition admonition-info\"><span class=\"admonition-info-text\"><b>Note:</b></span>\nThis requires the <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://github.com/nim-lang/fusion\">fusion</a> package.</div>\n<p><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://nim-lang.github.io/fusion/src/fusion/matching.html\">fusion/matching</a> supports pattern matching on <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt>s, with the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Some</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"Identifier\">pattern</span><span class=\"Operator\">&gt;</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt> and <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">None</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt> patterns.</p>\n<p><pre class=\"listing\"><span class=\"Punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">experimental</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"StringLit\">&quot;caseStmtMacros&quot;</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"Keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">fusion</span><span class=\"Operator\">/</span><span class=\"Identifier\">matching</span>\n\n<span class=\"Keyword\">case</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">some</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"DecNumber\">42</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"Keyword\">of</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">Some</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Operator\">@</span><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"Identifier\">assert</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">a</span> <span class=\"Operator\">==</span> <span class=\"DecNumber\">42</span>\n<span class=\"Keyword\">of</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">None</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"Identifier\">assert</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">false</span>\n\n<span class=\"Identifier\">assertMatch</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">some</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">some</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">none</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">int</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">Some</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">Some</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">None</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></pre></p>\n","entries":[{"name":"Option","type":"skType","line":91,"col":13,"code":"Option[T] = object\n  when T is SomePointer:\n  else:","description":"An optional type that may or may not contain a value of type <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span></span></tt>. When <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span></span></tt> is a a pointer type (<tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Keyword\">ptr</span></span></tt>, <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">pointer</span></span></tt>, <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Keyword\">ref</span></span></tt>, <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Keyword\">proc</span></span></tt> or <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Keyword\">iterator</span> <span class=\"Punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">closure</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">}</span></span></tt>), <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">none</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt> is represented as <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Keyword\">nil</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"UnpackDefect","type":"skType","line":101,"col":16,"code":"UnpackDefect = object of Defect"},{"name":"UnpackError","type":"skType","line":102,"col":58,"code":"UnpackError {.deprecated: \"See corresponding Defect\".} = UnpackDefect"},{"name":"option","type":"skProc","line":104,"col":0,"code":"proc option[T](val: sink T): Option[T] {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"Option[T]","arguments":[{"name":"val","type":"sink T"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Can be used to convert a pointer type (<tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Keyword\">ptr</span></span></tt>, <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">pointer</span></span></tt>, <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Keyword\">ref</span></span></tt> or <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Keyword\">proc</span></span></tt>) to an option type. It converts <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Keyword\">nil</span></span></tt> to <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">none</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt>. When <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">T</span></span></tt> is no pointer type, this is equivalent to <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">some</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">val</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#some,T\">some proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#none,typedesc\">none proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"some","type":"skProc","line":125,"col":0,"code":"proc some[T](val: sink T): Option[T] {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"Option[T]","arguments":[{"name":"val","type":"sink T"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Returns an <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt> that has the value <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">val</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#option,T\">option proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#none,typedesc\">none proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#isSome,Option[T]\">isSome proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"none","type":"skProc","line":144,"col":0,"code":"proc none(T: typedesc): Option[T] {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"Option[T]","arguments":[{"name":"T","type":"typedesc"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T:type","types":"None"}]},"description":"<p>Returns an <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt> for this type that has no value.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#option,T\">option proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#some,T\">some proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#isNone,Option[T]\">isNone proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"none","type":"skProc","line":157,"col":0,"code":"proc none[T](): Option[T] {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"Option[T]","pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Alias for <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#none,typedesc\">none(T)</a>."},{"name":"isSome","type":"skProc","line":161,"col":0,"code":"proc isSome[T](self: Option[T]): bool {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"Option[T]"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Checks if an <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt> contains a value.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#isNone,Option[T]\">isNone proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#some,T\">some proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"isNone","type":"skProc","line":176,"col":0,"code":"proc isNone[T](self: Option[T]): bool {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"Option[T]"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Checks if an <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt> is empty.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#isSome,Option[T]\">isSome proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#none,typedesc\">none proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"get","type":"skProc","line":191,"col":0,"code":"proc get[T](self: Option[T]): lent T {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"lent T","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"Option[T]"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Returns the content of an <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt>. If it has no value, an <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">UnpackDefect</span></span></tt> exception is raised.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#get,Option[T],T\">get proc</a> with a default return value</li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"get","type":"skProc","line":206,"col":0,"code":"proc get[T](self: Option[T]; otherwise: T): T {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"T","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"Option[T]"},{"name":"otherwise","type":"T"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Returns the content of the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt> or <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">otherwise</span></span></tt> if the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt> has no value."},{"name":"get","type":"skProc","line":218,"col":0,"code":"proc get[T](self: var Option[T]): var T {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"var T","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"var Option[T]"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Returns the content of the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Keyword\">var</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt> mutably. If it has no value, an <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">UnpackDefect</span></span></tt> exception is raised."},{"name":"map","type":"skProc","line":234,"col":0,"code":"proc map[T](self: Option[T]; callback: proc (input: T)) {.inline,\n    effectsOf: callback.}","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"Option[T]"},{"name":"callback","type":"proc (input: T)"}],"pragmas":["inline","effectsOf: callback"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Applies a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">callback</span></span></tt> function to the value of the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt>, if it has one.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#map,Option[T],proc(T)_2\">map proc</a> for a version with a callback which returns a value</li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"map","type":"skProc","line":253,"col":0,"code":"proc map[T, R](self: Option[T]; callback: proc (input: T): R): Option[R] {.\n    inline, effectsOf: callback.}","signature":{"return":"Option[R]","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"Option[T]"},{"name":"callback","type":"proc (input: T): R"}],"pragmas":["inline","effectsOf: callback"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"},{"name":"R"}]},"description":"<p>Applies a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">callback</span></span></tt> function to the value of the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt> and returns an <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt> containing the new value.</p>\n<p>If the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt> has no value, <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">none</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">R</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt> will be returned.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#map,Option[T],proc(T)\">map proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#flatMap,Option[T],proc(T)\">flatMap proc</a> for a version with a callback that returns an <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"flatten","type":"skProc","line":275,"col":0,"code":"proc flatten[T](self: Option[Option[T]]): Option[T] {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"Option[T]","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"Option[Option[T]]"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Remove one level of structure in a nested <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#flatMap,Option[T],proc(T)\">flatMap proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"flatMap","type":"skProc","line":289,"col":0,"code":"proc flatMap[T, R](self: Option[T]; callback: proc (input: T): Option[R]): Option[\n    R] {.inline, effectsOf: callback.}","signature":{"return":"Option[R]","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"Option[T]"},{"name":"callback","type":"proc (input: T): Option[R]"}],"pragmas":["inline","effectsOf: callback"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"},{"name":"R"}]},"description":"<p>Applies a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">callback</span></span></tt> function to the value of the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt> and returns the new value.</p>\n<p>If the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt> has no value, <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">none</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">R</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt> will be returned.</p>\n<p>This is similar to <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">map</span></span></tt>, with the difference that the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">callback</span></span></tt> returns an <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt>, not a raw value. This allows multiple procs with a signature of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">A</span> <span class=\"Operator\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">B</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt> to be chained together.</p>\n<p>See also:</p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#flatten,Option[Option[A]]\">flatten proc</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#filter,Option[T],proc(T)\">filter proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"filter","type":"skProc","line":315,"col":0,"code":"proc filter[T](self: Option[T]; callback: proc (input: T): bool): Option[T] {.\n    inline, effectsOf: callback.}","signature":{"return":"Option[T]","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"Option[T]"},{"name":"callback","type":"proc (input: T): bool"}],"pragmas":["inline","effectsOf: callback"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Applies a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">callback</span></span></tt> to the value of the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p>If the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">callback</span></span></tt> returns <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">true</span></span></tt>, the option is returned as <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">some</span></span></tt>. If it returns <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">false</span></span></tt>, it is returned as <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">none</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#flatMap,Option[A],proc(A)\">flatMap proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"`==`","type":"skProc","line":336,"col":0,"code":"proc `==`[T](a, b: Option[T]): bool {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"a","type":"Option[T]"},{"name":"b","type":"Option[T]"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Returns <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">true</span></span></tt> if both <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt>s are <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">none</span></span></tt>, or if they are both <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">some</span></span></tt> and have equal values."},{"name":"`$`","type":"skProc","line":355,"col":0,"code":"proc `$`[T](self: Option[T]): string","signature":{"return":"string","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"Option[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Get the string representation of the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Option</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"unsafeGet","type":"skProc","line":374,"col":0,"code":"proc unsafeGet[T](self: Option[T]): lent T {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"lent T","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"Option[T]"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Returns the value of a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">some</span></span></tt>. The behavior is undefined for <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">none</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Use this only when you are <strong>absolutely sure</strong> the value is present (e.g. after checking with <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#isSome,Option[T]\">isSome</a>). Generally, using the <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#get,Option[T]\">get proc</a> is preferred.</p>\n"}]}